{"id":14880794,"mediaExerciseId":"ee539f98-9418-4d5a-8ec8-b7b3f95baa60","exerciseName":"11","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612274,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":85,"solutions":[{"id":5925350,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine the problem in reporting the cash flow from the sale of treasury securities in the cash from operations section of the statement of cash flows.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":98,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/22/d922a82773846f9f80c0557ca64ac8dd/3762697fd9e2d378b580e36f75a740e6/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/22/d922a82773846f9f80c0557ca64ac8dd/3762697fd9e2d378b580e36f75a740e6/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define financing activities.\n\n**Financing activities** are activities involving long-term liabilities and equity, and borrowing or repaying short-term borrowings.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/22/d922a82773846f9f80c0557ca64ac8dd/c4ac8f13f59ed04d5b0986bf426e1685/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/22/d922a82773846f9f80c0557ca64ac8dd/c4ac8f13f59ed04d5b0986bf426e1685/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Manufacturing companies should have reported the cash flow from the sale of Treasury securities in the cash from financing section of the statement of cash flows instead of the cash from operations. \n\nThe company receives cash or cash equivalents against the shares from the new shareholder for a sale of treasury securities, therefore should be reported in the financing activities section of the statement of cash flows.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":216,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/22/d922a82773846f9f80c0557ca64ac8dd/235489c8afe2bcf45ec02436b8828691/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/22/d922a82773846f9f80c0557ca64ac8dd/235489c8afe2bcf45ec02436b8828691/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"ff32a4ca-4378-426f-a0de-cc6c39b169f0","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880795,"exerciseName":"12","page":85,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"5db24ed5-aec7-4c48-b6f7-8e5dc20c8113","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-critical-thinking-questions-12-5db24ed5-aec7-4c48-b6f7-8e5dc20c8113"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880793,"exerciseName":"10","page":84,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"3c4565d6-1420-4b95-b336-53a4c8b11a26","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundam